This is a perceptron POS tagger that uses viterbi decoding.
The data can be downloaded here: https://s3.amazonaws.com/MyT.practice/Data.zip
This was created for this assignment: http://cs.nyu.edu/~dsontag/courses/pgm13/assignments/ps7.pdf
an overview of results can be found here: https://s3.amazonaws.com/MyT.practice/Perceptron.docx

If you want to test this file out, you will run the file HW7FeaturesTry3.py in a directory that has a ./Data directory
as used in line 119 of HW7FeaturesTry3.py. You will also need the file ViterbiTry2.py in the directory as well.

A few things:

-You can train on up to 5000 sentences. Change the starting point of where you train (in offset by 100) with offSetTrainingSentences
in HW7FeaturesTry3.py. If you want fully trained results then set it to 48.
-You can change the number of perceptrons being trained by changing numProcesses in HW7FeaturesTry3.py. 
Especially useful if you want to see performance vs. number of training sentences.

